                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm is a detrimental spell.
<br />

<br />
You cannot cast detrimental spells on your pet.
<br />

<br />
Ergo, charm cannot be "refreshed" like other detrimental spells because of it's effect, charm. 
<br />

<br />
Unless there was a bug at one time where Charm wasn't considered a detrimental pell, or you could cast detrimental spells on your pet, this should not have ever been possible.  Although, the argument could be made that since most other detrimental spells (Can't think of any atm that don't) can be refreshed before they were off the target.  However, in light of SoE's views on a balanced charm, I doubt they would consider it.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=615243" target="_blank" class="postlink">Culbryz</a> 
<br />
